BOVINE TUBERCULOSIS - ISRAEL (02): (HAZAFON) CATTLE, ALERT, TYPING PENDING
**************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Mon 18 Mar 2019
Source: Veterinary Services & Animal Health, Min. of Agriculture, Notifications [in Hebrew, trans. Mod.AS, edited]
https://www.moag.gov.il/vet/Yechidot/VetBasade/Pirsumim/2019/Pages/shahefet_maoz_haim-18-3-19.aspx


During a routine slaughter of [4] mature dairy cows from Kibbutz Maoz Hayim, in an abbatoir, pathological changes suspected to be indicative of tuberculosis were discovered. The suspected material was forwarded to the Veterinary Institute, Beit-Dagan, where presumptive confirmation was obtained; samples submited to the Ministry of Health's TB Laboratory (National laboratory) in Abu Kabir were found there to be _Mycobacteriun tuberculosis complex_ positive. Further investigation to define/type the specific pathogen has been undertaken; its completion will take some time.

The farm of origin has been put under quarantine. Last week, all animals on the said dairy farm older than 6 months were tested by the delayed hypersensitivity test (Tuberculine); the results were read yesterday [Sun 17 Mar 2019], when 36 adult cows and 10 calves [older than 6 months] were found positive. All [46 cattle] were due to be culled today [18 Mar 2019].

--
